Spaghetti and BEET balls! I used the Post Punk Kitchen’s beet meat from their ‘Quarter Pounder Beet Burger’ recipe and rolled the result into balls. After a roll in some panko bread crumbs, I baked the balls until the crumbs were golden and tossed them on top of some spaghetti noodles and red sauce.

I came across Vegetarian Times’ Vegetables Wellington Redux recipe last week and decided I had to jump on top of an opportunity to use a puff pastry without a meaty base. Instead of using a loaf pan, I decided to make things a little more fancy and add some latice work on top. This was delicious, but I think I’m going to play around with the fillings next time.

While m’lady was away on business, I decided to indulge in a little extra red meat, so I ordered a couple french lamb chops and went to work. I made a quick curried dry rub and coated the chops before letting them come to room temp. After pan searing the lamb to medium rare, I used some milk, veggie broth, cornstarch and spices to make a quick pan sauce. I tossed some steamed cauliflower in the sauce and went to town.
